{"parse":{"title":"Giornata","pageid":15040304,"revid":839201118,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ignudo_02_detail.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Ignudo_02_detail.jpg/200px-Ignudo_02_detail.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"220\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Ignudo_02_detail.jpg/300px-Ignudo_02_detail.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/44/Ignudo_02_detail.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"386\" data-file-height=\"425\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ignudo_02_detail.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>the line formed by the giornata can be seen along the arm, head and back of this figure, from the <a href=\"/wiki/Sistine_Chapel_ceiling\" title=\"Sistine Chapel ceiling\">Sistine Chapel ceiling</a>, painted by <a href=\"/wiki/Michelangelo\" title=\"Michelangelo\">Michelangelo</a></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Giornata</b>  is an art term, originating from an Italian word which means \"a day's work.\"  The term is used in <a href=\"/wiki/Buon_fresco\" title=\"Buon fresco\">Buon fresco</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Mural_painting\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mural painting\">mural painting</a> and describes how much painting can be done in a single day of painting. Knowing how much can be painted in a day is crucial in the Buon fresco technique, because in this technique a watercolor paint, without binder, is applied to wet <a href=\"/wiki/Lime_plaster\" title=\"Lime plaster\">lime plaster</a> which binds the paint into the surface of the plaster when it dries, making for an extremely durable painting. An experienced fresco painter knows how much surface can be painted in a day, and wet plaster is applied to the wall in the right amount needed for each day's work.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> That amount is the <i>giornata</i>. Generally the plaster is applied in a way that will conform to the  outline of a figure, or object, in a painting, so that the daily segments will not show, but it is occasionally visible as different sections in a work where the artist may not have been able to replicate a pigment exactly the next day, or where restoration has altered or made apparent the changes in pigment between the sections.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notable_examples_giornate\">Notable examples giornate</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Giornata&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Notable examples giornate\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Masaccio-TheExpulsionOfAdamAndEveFromEden-Restoration.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Masaccio-TheExpulsionOfAdamAndEveFromEden-Restoration.jpg/220px-Masaccio-TheExpulsionOfAdamAndEveFromEden-Restoration.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"283\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Masaccio-TheExpulsionOfAdamAndEveFromEden-Restoration.jpg/330px-Masaccio-TheExpulsionOfAdamAndEveFromEden-Restoration.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Masaccio-TheExpulsionOfAdamAndEveFromEden-Restoration.jpg/440px-Masaccio-TheExpulsionOfAdamAndEveFromEden-Restoration.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"913\" data-file-height=\"1173\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Masaccio-TheExpulsionOfAdamAndEveFromEden-Restoration.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>An image showing how the recent restoration of <a href=\"/wiki/Masaccio\" title=\"Masaccio\">Masaccio</a>'s \"<i>Expulsion</i>\" made the giornata clearer - note the seam of darker blue pigment around the figure of Adam</div></div></div> <p><a href=\"/wiki/Masaccio\" title=\"Masaccio\">Masaccio</a>'s <i><a href=\"/wiki/Expulsion_from_the_Garden_of_Eden\" title=\"Expulsion from the Garden of Eden\">Expulsion from the Garden of Eden</a></i> - It is clearly visible that the figures of Adam and Eve were painted separately from the rest of the image, and indeed that the two figures themselves were painted separately from each other.\n</p><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:266px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Giotto_-_Scrovegni_-_-36-_-_Lamentation_(The_Mourning_of_Christ)_adj.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Giotto_-_Scrovegni_-_-36-_-_Lamentation_%28The_Mourning_of_Christ%29_adj.jpg/264px-Giotto_-_Scrovegni_-_-36-_-_Lamentation_%28The_Mourning_of_Christ%29_adj.jpg\" width=\"264\" height=\"244\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Giotto_-_Scrovegni_-_-36-_-_Lamentation_%28The_Mourning_of_Christ%29_adj.jpg/396px-Giotto_-_Scrovegni_-_-36-_-_Lamentation_%28The_Mourning_of_Christ%29_adj.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Giotto_-_Scrovegni_-_-36-_-_Lamentation_%28The_Mourning_of_Christ%29_adj.jpg/528px-Giotto_-_Scrovegni_-_-36-_-_Lamentation_%28The_Mourning_of_Christ%29_adj.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1000\" data-file-height=\"925\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Giotto_-_Scrovegni_-_-36-_-_Lamentation_(The_Mourning_of_Christ)_adj.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Note the lines in the sky and around the female figure clasping her hands. From the <a href=\"/wiki/Scrovegni_Chapel\" title=\"Scrovegni Chapel\">Arena Chapel</a>, painted by Giotto.</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Giotto\" title=\"Giotto\">Giotto</a>'s Frescoes in <a href=\"/wiki/Scrovegni_Chapel\" title=\"Scrovegni Chapel\">Arena Chapel</a> - It is clearly visible particularly in the Lamentation panel. The sky is broken up into several pieces and there are faint lines of demarcation visible around several of the figures.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Giornata&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.fresco-techniques.com/fresco-cartoon.html\"><i>Fresco Cartoon - Directions</i></a> fresco-techniques.com</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Vincent_Willem_van_Gogh_107.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/Vincent_Willem_van_Gogh_107.jpg/30px-Vincent_Willem_van_Gogh_107.jpg\" width=\"30\" height=\"37\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/Vincent_Willem_van_Gogh_107.jpg/45px-Vincent_Willem_van_Gogh_107.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/Vincent_Willem_van_Gogh_107.jpg/60px-Vincent_Willem_van_Gogh_107.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1256\" data-file-height=\"1539\" /></a></td><td><i>This article related to <a href=\"/wiki/Art\" title=\"Art\">art techniques</a> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Giornata&amp;action=edit\">expandin